        <mxCell id="77KPwD5JUIfZxNA-zf42-31" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=20;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=center;" value="Need basic layout block and visible UI in Strapi for this plugin&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;so what to do first ?? 🤔&lt;br&gt;Strapi cms plugin??&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="250" width="250" x="1330" y="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="77KPwD5JUIfZxNA-zf42-32" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=20;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;What will we have in that plugin: PLUGIN project name: CHEAP cli&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;1. data model for Component and Page config??&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;2. expose API to return page and component config via api??&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;3.A small puck app for user to edit.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;4. component config pushed how? api? or a small CLI app to sync config from a predefined folder structure?? -- CLI will look for strapi write access token and Strapi api app&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;5. CLI will sync changes from current folder structure with options - write the cli in go - use cobra frame work https://cobra.dev/:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;- fetch : fetch diff in components and remote page config settings, print the diff in std out&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;- pull &amp;lt;arg: component | page&amp;gt; &amp;lt;--name -n&amp;gt; &amp;lt;arg:component | page n ame&amp;gt; : pull specific component or page name&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;- pull &amp;lt;arg: component | page&amp;gt; --all: pull all changes from remote and apply to local folder structure, this will default to pull and replace everything in local folder&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;- push : push local change to remote Strapi server&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;- push --force : apply everything to remote Strapi server - this should have a confirmation prompt to proceed every time;; or could by pass with -y --yes-to-all to by pass cli&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;options:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;--force -f: force push everything to remote&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;--out -o : indicate where to store the pull data&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;--yes-to-all -Y : by pass any confirmation prompt with yes&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;--all -a : pull everything&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;--host -H : remote content api server, anything that support this api interface; will look for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;--authorization-token -T : authorization token to put as Bearer token,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
